            <div type="a">
                <column>2</column>
                <head>County Levy</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Kinney</ln>
                        <pf>Mr.</pf>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>June Court arranged the county levy for the year. Population has dropped by
                    about 300 people, because of Western emigration, and consequently the levy is
                    higher--$1.87 1/2, up from $1.62 1/2 last year.</summary>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>2</column>
                <head>Augusta County Jail</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Armentrout</ln>
                        <pf>Geo. A.</pf>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>324 people, black and white, committed to jail last year for a variety of
                    reasons. Number one, public drunkeness (80 people). 152 slaves were committed
                    for "safe keeping" by masters, traders or the Sheriff.</summary>
            </div>
